                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-856" type="given" value="MAURICE"></interp>MAURICE MONSANTO</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a merchant, and live in the Strand. A little past eight o'clock, on the night of the 25th of Sept., I was looking at a print-shop in the Strand, and felt my handkerchief taken from my pocket—I turned round, and saw the prisoner with it under his coat—I took it from him, and he escaped—I am sure he is the man—I had seen it safe two or three minutes before.</p>
